WEBVTT

1
00:00:08.750 --> 00:00:11.750
[The Watcher] <i>New York. December 1991.</i>

2
00:00:11.833 --> 00:00:16.000
<i>The night the Winter Soldier came
to assassinate Howard and Maria Stark.</i>

3
00:00:16.542 --> 00:00:18.125
<i>But in this universe.</i>

4
00:00:18.833 --> 00:00:22.208
<i>how could a night so pivotal
in the lives of the Avengers.</i>

5
00:00:22.292 --> 00:00:25.500
<i>an event whose ramifications
would be felt for decades.</i>

6
00:00:26.083 --> 00:00:29.042
<i>how could it have gone so differently?</i>

7
00:00:33.375 --> 00:00:34.417
[The Watcher] <i>Time.</i>

8
00:00:37.875 --> 00:00:38.958
<i>Space.</i>

9
00:00:40.708 --> 00:00:41.750
<i>Reality.</i>

10
00:00:44.625 --> 00:00:46.292
<i>It's more than a linear path.</i>

11
00:00:51.167 --> 00:00:55.667
<i>It's a prism of endless possibility.</i>

12
00:00:58.208 --> 00:01:01.625
<i>where a single choice
can branch out into infinite realities.</i>

13
00:01:04.417 --> 00:01:07.167
<i>creating alternate worlds
from the ones you know.</i>

14
00:01:11.292 --> 00:01:12.625
<i>I am the Watcher.</i>

15
00:01:14.875 --> 00:01:18.042
<i>I am your guide
through these vast new realities.</i>

16
00:01:19.458 --> 00:01:22.958
<i>Follow me and ponder the question...</i>

17
00:01:26.625 --> 00:01:28.250
<i>"What if?"</i>

18
00:01:30.875 --> 00:01:33.500
[Red Guardian]
<i>You've got to be kidding me.</i>

19
00:01:34.417 --> 00:01:39.208
You want me to go undercover
as a Data Input Manager

20
00:01:39.708 --> 00:01:43.667
-in Ohio?
-Senior Data Input Manager. Eh?

21
00:01:43.750 --> 00:01:45.500
Middle management ain't too shabby.

22
00:01:45.583 --> 00:01:50.167
I am the Red Guardian.
I am Mother Russia's first super-soldier.

23
00:01:50.250 --> 00:01:54.167
You know my worth. my talent.
and yet you ask this of me?

24
00:01:54.250 --> 00:01:56.625
It's a pretty top-priority mission.

25
00:01:56.708 --> 00:01:58.750
Horseradish! I am no fool.

26
00:01:58.833 --> 00:02:02.458
I've heard the rumors.
Whispers in the halls.

27
00:02:02.542 --> 00:02:04.417
The Rook has sent new intel.

28
00:02:04.500 --> 00:02:06.208
I've never heard of this crook.

29
00:02:06.292 --> 00:02:07.958
Rook! It's a chess piece.

30
00:02:08.042 --> 00:02:11.417
Dreykov. don't play dumb with me
when I'm obviously smarter than you.

31
00:02:11.500 --> 00:02:14.542
I am speaking of the Rook.
the American sleeper agent.

32
00:02:14.625 --> 00:02:17.958
-has intel on a high-value target.
-[phone ringing]

33
00:02:18.042 --> 00:02:19.708
Uh. General Dreykov.

34
00:02:20.042 --> 00:02:22.750
Aah! <i>Da.</i> Karpov.

35
00:02:22.833 --> 00:02:24.375
Eh. there's a mission.

36
00:02:24.458 --> 00:02:26.500
I need you to defrost the...

37
00:02:26.583 --> 00:02:27.917
the Winter Soldier.

38
00:02:28.000 --> 00:02:32.167
The Winter Soldier?
That piece of HYDRA trash!

39
00:02:32.250 --> 00:02:35.250
-I appreciate it. Karpov.
-He's not even real Russian.

40
00:02:35.333 --> 00:02:39.792
Hey. hey. hey.
We're all a team here. Family.

41
00:02:39.875 --> 00:02:42.792
Don't be mad
that your brother has a different mission.

42
00:02:42.875 --> 00:02:44.000
Celebrate him. huh?

43
00:02:44.083 --> 00:02:48.083
Huh. Maybe it's time for the Red Guardian
to spread his wings.

44
00:02:48.167 --> 00:02:52.208
Go somewhere
that will appreciate my skills!

45
00:02:52.292 --> 00:02:54.583
Celebrate that. Dreykov!

46
00:02:54.667 --> 00:02:55.792
What you're going to do. huh?

47
00:02:55.875 --> 00:02:58.208
Put in an application at S.H.I.E.L.D.?
[scoffs]

48
00:02:58.792 --> 00:03:03.208
Then the Red Guardian
shall demonstrate his value once again.

49
00:03:03.917 --> 00:03:04.917
All right.

50
00:03:06.500 --> 00:03:09.333
["Le Chemin" by Alexandrov Ensemble
& Boris Alexandrov playing]

51
00:03:09.417 --> 00:03:10.833
[grumbles]

52
00:03:12.375 --> 00:03:13.792
[speaking Russian]

53
00:03:30.000 --> 00:03:31.250
[console beeping]

54
00:03:31.792 --> 00:03:33.208
[speaking English] Ready to comply.

55
00:03:33.292 --> 00:03:34.458
[music continues]

56
00:03:34.542 --> 00:03:36.125
[screams]

57
00:03:41.833 --> 00:03:43.792
-[female officer] Name?
-I am... Uh...

58
00:03:43.875 --> 00:03:45.833
-Uh. Bob Toledo.
-Business or pleasure?

59
00:03:45.917 --> 00:03:49.792
Well. I come for the pleasure
of doing business.

60
00:03:49.875 --> 00:03:51.292
[both laugh]

61
00:03:51.375 --> 00:03:52.708
Wise guy.

62
00:04:07.667 --> 00:04:08.750
[engine starts]

63
00:04:10.375 --> 00:04:11.542
[accelerating]

64
00:04:17.167 --> 00:04:18.750
[car. tires screeching. thuds]

65
00:04:18.833 --> 00:04:20.833
-[panting. groans]
-[shield clangs]

66
00:04:22.417 --> 00:04:25.750
Whoa. whoa. whoa!
The mission is to steal the fancy serum.

67
00:04:26.875 --> 00:04:27.875
No witnesses.

68
00:04:27.958 --> 00:04:31.792
No murder. The Red Guardian
is Russia's greatest super-spy.

69
00:04:31.875 --> 00:04:34.708
Anyone can kill. Bang-bang. easy-peasy.

70
00:04:34.792 --> 00:04:39.042
but I am the night and I am the wind.

71
00:04:39.125 --> 00:04:42.125
I am here.
and then vanish without a trace.

72
00:04:42.708 --> 00:04:45.625
-No witnesses.
-Yes. witnesses.

73
00:04:45.708 --> 00:04:49.167
This way Stark runs back
to his capitalist pig friends

74
00:04:49.250 --> 00:04:53.667
and warns them that the revolution
is coming and he wears red.

75
00:04:53.750 --> 00:04:55.250
And white.

76
00:04:55.333 --> 00:04:57.833
And that you were here too. Da?

77
00:04:57.917 --> 00:04:59.125
-[gunshots. ricochets]
-Hyah!

78
00:05:00.333 --> 00:05:01.833
Behold my technique.

79
00:05:01.917 --> 00:05:03.375
Hyah!

80
00:05:05.542 --> 00:05:06.750
[laughs. groans]

81
00:05:08.333 --> 00:05:09.667
[laughs. groans]

82
00:05:09.750 --> 00:05:11.083
The Red...

83
00:05:11.167 --> 00:05:13.083
[groans]

84
00:05:13.167 --> 00:05:14.500
Technique.

85
00:05:14.625 --> 00:05:16.042
[thuds. vibrating]

86
00:05:16.125 --> 00:05:17.917
Well. not bad.

87
00:05:19.333 --> 00:05:20.333
Boom!

88
00:05:21.125 --> 00:05:23.958
[screams] Biting is cheating.

89
00:05:24.042 --> 00:05:25.375
[both grunting]

90
00:05:25.458 --> 00:05:27.125
[sirens approaching]

91
00:05:32.375 --> 00:05:33.917
[screams]

92
00:05:34.000 --> 00:05:36.292
[beeping]

93
00:05:37.417 --> 00:05:39.417
[radio chatter in distance]

94
00:05:41.958 --> 00:05:45.625
Oh. I have one of those. too.
Heavy. though. I left it in my luggage.

95
00:05:45.708 --> 00:05:48.042
-Is that the XZ-Eight?
-Ten.

96
00:05:48.125 --> 00:05:49.542
-Ten?
-XZ-Ten.

97
00:05:49.625 --> 00:05:51.458
What happened to the nine?

98
00:05:51.958 --> 00:05:54.417
Was there a nine? I didn't get a nine.

99
00:05:54.500 --> 00:05:56.167
[Karpov] <i>Did you secure the package?</i>

100
00:05:57.458 --> 00:05:59.500
One out of three ain't bad.

101
00:05:59.583 --> 00:06:01.417
Negative. We secured one.

102
00:06:01.500 --> 00:06:02.583
<i>No witnesses?</i>

103
00:06:02.667 --> 00:06:04.958
There were... complications.

104
00:06:05.500 --> 00:06:08.792
<i>You have failed your mission. soldier.
Your team has been compromised.</i>

105
00:06:08.875 --> 00:06:10.458
<i>-You're on your own for extraction.</i>
-What?

106
00:06:10.542 --> 00:06:11.958
<i>-Over.</i>
-[groans]

107
00:06:12.042 --> 00:06:13.792
Typical Red Room borscht.

108
00:06:13.875 --> 00:06:15.917
They say they care. but do they?

109
00:06:16.417 --> 00:06:17.500
[blows raspberry]

110
00:06:17.583 --> 00:06:20.500
Mission failure? I never fail.

111
00:06:25.458 --> 00:06:26.458
[knocks]

112
00:06:26.542 --> 00:06:28.542
[siren blaring]

113
00:06:30.750 --> 00:06:31.750
Listen up.

114
00:06:31.833 --> 00:06:34.917
The name is Dr. Bill Foster. I'm the head
of the S.H.I.E.L.D. Science Division

115
00:06:35.000 --> 00:06:37.000
which makes me the primary
on this investigation.

116
00:06:37.083 --> 00:06:38.500
Who was first on the scene?

117
00:06:38.583 --> 00:06:39.625
That would be me.

118
00:06:39.708 --> 00:06:41.958
-Talk to me. Ranger.
-Ranger Morales. sir.

119
00:06:42.042 --> 00:06:43.625
-Mm-hm.
-Howard and Maria Stark.

120
00:06:43.708 --> 00:06:46.667
Concussions. lacerations.
but expected to make a full recovery.

121
00:06:46.750 --> 00:06:48.500
-Great. What'd they see?
-Um. not much.

122
00:06:48.583 --> 00:06:51.333
The wife was unconscious.
The husband saw two men fighting.

123
00:06:51.417 --> 00:06:53.667
Best guess would have been
a carjacking gone wrong.

124
00:06:53.750 --> 00:06:55.000
"Best guess"?

125
00:06:55.083 --> 00:06:58.083
Ranger. in my world.
we don't get the luxury of guessing.

126
00:06:58.167 --> 00:07:00.958
Yes. but that trail
of blue Cookie Monster blood

127
00:07:01.042 --> 00:07:02.667
has me thinking it's a little worse

128
00:07:02.750 --> 00:07:04.750
than a couple of knuckleheads
out for a joyride.

129
00:07:04.833 --> 00:07:06.875
-Mm-hm.
-What's that gunk anyway?

130
00:07:06.958 --> 00:07:09.750
This gunk can change
the course of history.

131
00:07:09.833 --> 00:07:11.375
-Seriously?
-Oh. yeah.

132
00:07:12.250 --> 00:07:13.833
Agents and officers.

133
00:07:13.917 --> 00:07:17.875
shut down the airports. train stations.
and bus stations.

134
00:07:17.958 --> 00:07:21.875
I want a hard perimeter stretching
from here to Ohio.

135
00:07:21.958 --> 00:07:25.667
We are dealing with
genetically. biologically. physically.

136
00:07:25.750 --> 00:07:29.000
and mechanically enhanced super-soldiers.

137
00:07:29.083 --> 00:07:33.000
These men are trained
to infiltrate and destroy.

138
00:07:33.083 --> 00:07:35.917
They are capable of the unthinkable.

139
00:07:36.000 --> 00:07:38.750
To face them is to face death.

140
00:07:38.833 --> 00:07:40.458
A-ha!

141
00:07:40.542 --> 00:07:44.583
Foisting capitalist greed
onto the working man!

142
00:07:44.667 --> 00:07:46.167
I don't blame you. sister.

143
00:07:46.250 --> 00:07:48.875
You've been brainwashed
by the bourgeoisie pigs

144
00:07:48.958 --> 00:07:51.583
who force you
into paper hats and servitude!

145
00:07:52.125 --> 00:07:55.167
Sir. All I asked
was if you wanted fries with that.

146
00:07:55.250 --> 00:07:57.708
Demand a revolution!

147
00:07:57.792 --> 00:08:00.125
Seize the means of production!

148
00:08:00.208 --> 00:08:03.292
The nuggets of chicken
are yours for the taking!

149
00:08:03.375 --> 00:08:06.000
-Alexei...
-Your masters have you slinging burgers.

150
00:08:06.083 --> 00:08:10.125
but when. when. when do you get to eat?

151
00:08:10.208 --> 00:08:12.208
I'm a vegetarian. fart-knocker!

152
00:08:12.292 --> 00:08:15.167
Hah. Hey. Lucy. is it?
That's a pretty name.

153
00:08:15.250 --> 00:08:19.042
Listen. my friend's had a rough night.
Can we get a couple sixes and two Cokes?

154
00:08:20.250 --> 00:08:22.958
Sure. I'll throw in some extra fries.

155
00:08:24.250 --> 00:08:26.125
What in the pelmeni was that?

156
00:08:26.208 --> 00:08:28.125
Your idiocy triggered my deep cover mode.

157
00:08:28.208 --> 00:08:31.292
Well. knock it off. Captain Personality.
You're embarrassing us.

158
00:08:31.375 --> 00:08:32.833
You're going to get us caught.

159
00:08:33.333 --> 00:08:34.792
[Red Guardian] Mmm.

160
00:08:36.292 --> 00:08:37.292
Mwah!

161
00:08:37.375 --> 00:08:41.042
I was liberating her mind.
Breaking her mental shackles.

162
00:08:41.792 --> 00:08:42.833
It's what I do.

163
00:08:43.417 --> 00:08:45.250
That's it. The Rook.

164
00:08:45.333 --> 00:08:48.583
The secret legend who will flip
the US hegemony like a <i>Monopoly</i> board.

165
00:08:48.667 --> 00:08:51.750
The man who will unite the workers
and reshape history.

166
00:08:51.833 --> 00:08:52.917
[chuckles]

167
00:08:53.000 --> 00:08:54.292
[Winter Soldier] Alexei.

168
00:08:56.375 --> 00:09:00.500
The Rook will help us.
Especially when he sees we have this.

169
00:09:00.583 --> 00:09:05.625
Ha-ha! Here. The most recent communiqué
has him in Last Vegas.

170
00:09:05.708 --> 00:09:06.708
It's Las Vegas.

171
00:09:06.792 --> 00:09:09.458
That's what I said.
It's very rude to correct my English.

172
00:09:09.542 --> 00:09:12.083
Obviously. they forgot
to program any manners into you.

173
00:09:12.167 --> 00:09:13.250
[slurping]

174
00:09:13.333 --> 00:09:16.708
-Now. we must acquire transport.
-[♪ rock music playing in distance]

175
00:09:16.792 --> 00:09:18.750
[tires screeching]

176
00:09:20.917 --> 00:09:21.917
[spits]

177
00:09:22.500 --> 00:09:24.542
Lenin smiles upon us.

178
00:09:31.708 --> 00:09:33.875
These fries are pretty good.

179
00:09:33.958 --> 00:09:37.792
They must be made from Russian potatoes.
Ha!

180
00:09:37.875 --> 00:09:39.625
Russia's the best.

181
00:09:40.292 --> 00:09:41.292
Oh.

182
00:09:49.583 --> 00:09:50.583
Hm.

183
00:09:51.250 --> 00:09:52.375
I'll handle this one.

184
00:09:53.000 --> 00:09:55.292
Relax. relax. The Red Guardian has this.

185
00:09:55.792 --> 00:09:58.208
Are you relaxing? It's very hard to tell.

186
00:09:58.292 --> 00:10:01.083
Your eyes so angry. like...

187
00:10:01.667 --> 00:10:02.667
Winter Fox.

188
00:10:04.750 --> 00:10:06.875
Uh. ah. how can I help you. officer?

189
00:10:06.958 --> 00:10:08.417
Just a routine check-in.

190
00:10:08.500 --> 00:10:10.333
Say. where are you fellas headed?

191
00:10:10.417 --> 00:10:12.583
[stuttering]

192
00:10:12.667 --> 00:10:16.208
-Sister's.
-Yes. to visit our sister.

193
00:10:16.292 --> 00:10:17.417
It's her birthday.

194
00:10:17.500 --> 00:10:18.833
You guys are brothers?

195
00:10:19.333 --> 00:10:21.208
What'd you get your sister
for her birthday?

196
00:10:21.292 --> 00:10:22.625
'Cause I cannot for the life of me

197
00:10:22.708 --> 00:10:24.417
figure out
what to get my wife for Christmas.

198
00:10:24.500 --> 00:10:25.625
-Sweater.
-Television.

199
00:10:25.708 --> 00:10:28.708
You got her a sweater and a television?

200
00:10:28.792 --> 00:10:31.292
Wow! That's very generous.

201
00:10:33.875 --> 00:10:37.375
Nice story.
but where are you really headed?

202
00:10:37.458 --> 00:10:40.292
[chuckles nervously]

203
00:10:41.042 --> 00:10:43.042
Step out of the vehicle
and keep your hands...

204
00:10:43.125 --> 00:10:44.917
-[screams]
-Whoa! Hey!

205
00:10:45.000 --> 00:10:46.000
[screech]

206
00:10:47.750 --> 00:10:51.667
Really? Again with the guns?
I had wool over his eyes.

207
00:10:52.583 --> 00:10:56.375
Target spotted. In pursuit.
Exercise caution. but get them.

208
00:10:57.542 --> 00:10:58.750
Get in. cowboy.

209
00:10:58.833 --> 00:11:01.250
Let's go round up some super-soldiers.

210
00:11:03.333 --> 00:11:07.708
[Red Guardian] Stop with the bullets.
You should dance with your enemies.

211
00:11:08.208 --> 00:11:11.917
It is like a great ballet of violence.

212
00:11:13.250 --> 00:11:14.250
[siren blaring]

213
00:11:14.333 --> 00:11:15.458
No!

214
00:11:15.542 --> 00:11:17.125
[indistinct]

215
00:11:17.208 --> 00:11:20.792
Where did that come from?
Did you have that the whole time?

216
00:11:22.417 --> 00:11:24.208
No. no. don't shoot!

217
00:11:24.292 --> 00:11:25.917
-Dance.
-Hey! Stop swerving!

218
00:11:36.583 --> 00:11:38.375
I told you. Dance!

219
00:11:38.458 --> 00:11:40.167
Hey! This is federal property.

220
00:11:40.250 --> 00:11:41.833
Come on. man.

221
00:11:42.750 --> 00:11:44.208
Dance! Dance!

222
00:11:47.167 --> 00:11:48.167
-It's jammed.
-You know

223
00:11:48.250 --> 00:11:49.792
what Karl Marx said about machines?

224
00:11:51.000 --> 00:11:52.667
They make men lazy.

225
00:11:53.625 --> 00:11:56.583
Stop! Stop! It's over.
Surrender yourselves.

226
00:11:56.667 --> 00:11:59.250
The Red Guardian never surrenders!

227
00:12:00.333 --> 00:12:01.333
Hands off!

228
00:12:03.042 --> 00:12:05.250
Dance technique!

229
00:12:06.208 --> 00:12:07.208
[screaming]

230
00:12:09.250 --> 00:12:11.167
[Red Guardian laughs]

231
00:12:11.250 --> 00:12:14.083
Winter Fox and the Red Guardian!

232
00:12:16.708 --> 00:12:18.083
Sir. what are you...

233
00:12:18.583 --> 00:12:20.292
You're never gonna catch them on foot.

234
00:12:21.875 --> 00:12:22.875
Whoa!

235
00:12:23.417 --> 00:12:25.458
Okay. sir. I see you.

236
00:12:33.167 --> 00:12:34.583
Ah. impressive.

237
00:12:37.667 --> 00:12:39.750
I'm sorry. farmers!

238
00:12:39.833 --> 00:12:42.458
Although of all the animals kept
by this farmer.

239
00:12:42.542 --> 00:12:45.583
it is the worker
who is most brutally treated!

240
00:12:45.667 --> 00:12:48.708
Again with the manifesto?
You're more brainwashed than me.

241
00:12:51.167 --> 00:12:54.750
Whoa! Winter Fox. We've got a big problem.

242
00:12:56.750 --> 00:12:59.667
[Goliath] Nowhere to go. baby.
Nowhere to run. Nowhere to hide.

243
00:12:59.750 --> 00:13:03.083
Why is everything so big in America?

244
00:13:03.167 --> 00:13:05.708
-[engine accelerating]
-[Red Guardian screams]

245
00:13:06.458 --> 00:13:09.083
-Sorry. chickens. Sorry. cows.
-[chickens clucking. cows mooing]

246
00:13:09.167 --> 00:13:10.167
[distant mooing]

247
00:13:22.667 --> 00:13:23.708
Take the wheel.

248
00:13:25.375 --> 00:13:27.708
Where are you? Where are... Yes!

249
00:13:27.792 --> 00:13:28.958
Mwah!

250
00:13:29.042 --> 00:13:30.833
We've got work to do.

251
00:13:35.583 --> 00:13:36.708
Technique!

252
00:13:36.792 --> 00:13:38.375
The bigger they are.

253
00:13:39.208 --> 00:13:42.208
the harder they fall.

254
00:13:44.875 --> 00:13:46.083
Ha-ha!

255
00:13:46.167 --> 00:13:49.500
This is a quality automobile.

256
00:13:49.583 --> 00:13:53.000
which is a credit
to the workers' union that built it.

257
00:13:58.125 --> 00:13:59.875
-Keep going?
-Why not?

258
00:13:59.958 --> 00:14:02.375
I have nowhere else to be today.

259
00:14:06.417 --> 00:14:07.417
They're not...

260
00:14:07.500 --> 00:14:11.750
Okay. these two are either the bravest
or dumbest men on the planet.

261
00:14:11.833 --> 00:14:14.083
Worse. Enhanced and dumb.

262
00:14:16.125 --> 00:14:19.000
[operatic chanting]

263
00:14:21.583 --> 00:14:24.125
[screaming]

264
00:14:25.292 --> 00:14:27.375
-[both gasp]
-[Winter Solider grunts]

265
00:14:27.458 --> 00:14:28.583
[gasps]

266
00:14:32.000 --> 00:14:34.000
[helicopter hovering]

267
00:14:34.083 --> 00:14:35.833
[dog barks distantly]

268
00:14:35.917 --> 00:14:37.458
[crickets chirping]

269
00:14:37.542 --> 00:14:38.542
[Morales] Found it!

270
00:14:40.083 --> 00:14:42.000
Hmm. You're still on the case. Ranger?

271
00:14:42.083 --> 00:14:44.875
The National Park Service
is a federal agency. sir.

272
00:14:44.958 --> 00:14:47.292
Besides. I once wrestled Bigfoot
with my bare hands.

273
00:14:47.375 --> 00:14:49.542
-What?
-Nah. it was just a mountain lion.

274
00:14:49.625 --> 00:14:51.875
But the point is.
these yahoos don't scare me.

275
00:14:51.958 --> 00:14:54.417
[chuckles softly] Uh-huh? I see you.

276
00:14:57.708 --> 00:15:00.500
-Is that a <i>Thomas Guide?</i>
-Mm.

277
00:15:00.583 --> 00:15:02.125
With a page missing.

278
00:15:02.208 --> 00:15:04.000
Looks like we're going to Vegas. baby.

279
00:15:04.583 --> 00:15:07.583
[siren wailing in distance]

280
00:15:08.667 --> 00:15:10.042
[Red Guardian] Hah.

281
00:15:10.125 --> 00:15:14.625
This... This will garner me
a commendation. maybe even a medal.

282
00:15:15.208 --> 00:15:16.208
Ah!

283
00:15:16.292 --> 00:15:18.792
You're hurt. Why didn't you say something?

284
00:15:18.875 --> 00:15:22.333
The Winter Soldier never complains.
only complies.

285
00:15:24.417 --> 00:15:27.208
Stop it.
You're scaring the kittens. Let me.

286
00:15:28.208 --> 00:15:29.542
[meows]

287
00:15:30.167 --> 00:15:31.167
You know. you're supposed

288
00:15:31.250 --> 00:15:34.250
to catch the bullets
with your metal arm. Hm?

289
00:15:34.333 --> 00:15:35.458
How'd that happen?

290
00:15:36.000 --> 00:15:37.500
How did you happen?

291
00:15:37.583 --> 00:15:40.833
I come from a family of nobodies.

292
00:15:40.917 --> 00:15:44.917
Good people but...
then I had the chance to become somebody.

293
00:15:45.458 --> 00:15:49.167
Now. I am Mother Russia's great protector.
her Red Guardian.

294
00:15:49.708 --> 00:15:52.792
Pretty good for a boy from nowhere. eh?

295
00:15:54.458 --> 00:15:57.500
I'm a nobody.
I can't even remember anything.

296
00:15:58.125 --> 00:15:59.375
[Red Guardian] Nothing?

297
00:15:59.458 --> 00:16:00.625
Not even my name.

298
00:16:00.708 --> 00:16:02.750
[Red Guardian] I don't believe that.

299
00:16:02.833 --> 00:16:06.417
Look at you.
You are strong man with big brain.

300
00:16:06.500 --> 00:16:07.750
-Close your eyes.
-No.

301
00:16:07.833 --> 00:16:08.833
-Close...
-No.

302
00:16:08.917 --> 00:16:10.500
Closey. close.

303
00:16:12.000 --> 00:16:15.417
-Okay. fine.
-Now. think. Think back.

304
00:16:15.500 --> 00:16:18.167
<i>What's the first thing you see?</i>

305
00:16:18.708 --> 00:16:20.042
[Winter Soldier] <i>I see...</i>

306
00:16:22.000 --> 00:16:23.083
<i>I see...</i>

307
00:16:32.083 --> 00:16:33.292
I see Coney Island.

308
00:16:33.375 --> 00:16:36.167
See! You are somebody.

309
00:16:36.250 --> 00:16:38.958
You are the great Coney Island hero.

310
00:16:39.042 --> 00:16:42.917
And the Red Guardian
is proud to fight next to you.

311
00:16:43.500 --> 00:16:46.750
-Thank you.
-I'm going to steal us a new ride.

312
00:16:46.833 --> 00:16:49.667
Maybe something nice.
Some heated seats. yeah?

313
00:16:53.667 --> 00:16:55.083
-[phone ringing]
-[sighs]

314
00:17:00.167 --> 00:17:01.500
Ready to comply.

315
00:17:01.583 --> 00:17:04.375
<i>Soldier. this is General Dreykov.</i>

316
00:17:04.458 --> 00:17:06.417
<i>Mission orders have changed.</i>

317
00:17:06.500 --> 00:17:10.833
<i>You're to dispose of
Agent Alexei Shostakov. the Red Guardian.</i>

318
00:17:10.917 --> 00:17:12.167
Repeat orders. sir?

319
00:17:12.250 --> 00:17:14.625
<i>Shostakov has become a liability.</i>

320
00:17:15.125 --> 00:17:18.292
<i>Put a bullet in his thick skull
and get back here.</i>

321
00:17:18.375 --> 00:17:19.375
<i>Do you copy?</i>

322
00:17:20.917 --> 00:17:25.833
<i>Do I need to remind you that
mission failure will not be tolerated?</i>

323
00:17:27.208 --> 00:17:28.292
No. sir.

324
00:17:35.917 --> 00:17:40.083
[sighs] All these lights!
Who's paying the electric bills?

325
00:17:40.167 --> 00:17:41.875
The worker. that is who.

326
00:17:42.458 --> 00:17:44.167
Maybe we should play some craps later.

327
00:17:44.708 --> 00:17:46.292
You know. to blend in?

328
00:17:46.375 --> 00:17:49.375
Yeah. but no all-you-can-eat buffets.

329
00:17:49.458 --> 00:17:50.917
You'll put them out of business.

330
00:17:52.417 --> 00:17:54.333
Ah! A smile. huh?

331
00:17:54.417 --> 00:17:55.792
[speaking Russian]

332
00:17:58.958 --> 00:18:00.833
[speaking English] Here we are. [pants]

333
00:18:00.917 --> 00:18:03.417
Shield. helmet. Um...

334
00:18:03.500 --> 00:18:04.500
[exhales] Okay.

335
00:18:04.583 --> 00:18:09.417
[inhales] Now. finally to meet the Rook.

336
00:18:09.958 --> 00:18:10.958
How do I look?

337
00:18:11.042 --> 00:18:13.250
You look good. Very Russian.

338
00:18:13.917 --> 00:18:16.000
May Lenin smile upon us.

339
00:18:17.417 --> 00:18:19.125
[The Rook] Come on in. It's open.

340
00:18:20.083 --> 00:18:23.167
Pop the cork. will ya?
I can shuck my own...

341
00:18:23.958 --> 00:18:26.708
Well. you're not room service.
What's going on?

342
00:18:26.792 --> 00:18:29.500
Comrade Rook. I am the Red Guardian. sir.

343
00:18:29.583 --> 00:18:32.458
This is my compatriot. the Winter Soldier.

344
00:18:32.542 --> 00:18:35.542
It is our honor to meet you.

345
00:18:35.625 --> 00:18:38.875
I thought he'd be taller.
Did you think that? Is that weird?

346
00:18:38.958 --> 00:18:40.583
Well. what are you?

347
00:18:40.667 --> 00:18:43.042
Why are you dressed like this?
Are you a...

348
00:18:43.125 --> 00:18:45.917
Is he gonna shoot you
out of a cannon later or...

349
00:18:46.000 --> 00:18:50.250
You are the nefarious Rook
who will bring Uncle Sam to his knees.

350
00:18:50.333 --> 00:18:53.458
You will ignite the revolution
that frees the proletariat.

351
00:18:54.250 --> 00:18:57.042
Wait. so you two are Rusky spies?

352
00:18:57.125 --> 00:18:59.125
What are you doing in my hotel room?

353
00:18:59.208 --> 00:19:03.000
Our mission was compromised.
We require transport back to Russia.

354
00:19:03.083 --> 00:19:07.750
Whoa. I am no Russian spy.
I am a hot-blooded American boy.

355
00:19:07.833 --> 00:19:10.000
You are the Rook!

356
00:19:10.083 --> 00:19:13.417
You strike fear
into the hearts and wallets...

357
00:19:13.500 --> 00:19:16.042
I feel like I'm speaking
a different language here.

358
00:19:16.125 --> 00:19:17.417
Okay. okay.

359
00:19:17.500 --> 00:19:21.875
Look. I traded the Russians some
information on Stark's hunky-dory serum.

360
00:19:21.958 --> 00:19:23.292
A little tit-for-tat.

361
00:19:23.375 --> 00:19:27.625
And in return. you two idiots
were supposed to kill the Starks!

362
00:19:27.708 --> 00:19:29.583
Now. I was supposed to be givin'

363
00:19:29.667 --> 00:19:32.208
a tear-filled eulogy
about the fool right now.

364
00:19:32.292 --> 00:19:34.750
while they scrape his name
off Stark Industries.

365
00:19:34.833 --> 00:19:39.000
But instead. Howard Stark's sitting
eatin' tapioca in a hospital.

366
00:19:39.083 --> 00:19:42.583
and I'm talking to you.
Stupid Siegfried and Angry Roy!

367
00:19:43.458 --> 00:19:44.458
What?

368
00:19:46.542 --> 00:19:47.542
You are...

369
00:19:48.917 --> 00:19:51.083
You are capitalist pig?

370
00:19:51.917 --> 00:19:54.458
Red Room work with capitalist pig?

371
00:19:55.958 --> 00:19:59.917
Red Guardian work for capitalist pig?

372
00:20:00.000 --> 00:20:02.375
Hey. listen. husky Rusky.

373
00:20:02.458 --> 00:20:05.250
capitalism is the only system

374
00:20:05.333 --> 00:20:10.625
that stands for a man's right to own
his work. his life. and his happiness.

375
00:20:10.708 --> 00:20:15.583
Any man who thinks money
is the root of all evil is obviously poor.

376
00:20:15.667 --> 00:20:19.250
Not a country on this planet
that doesn't run on greed.

377
00:20:19.333 --> 00:20:20.333
Tell me something.

378
00:20:20.417 --> 00:20:26.625
You think your bosses. your comrades
give two nickels about you? Hm?

379
00:20:26.708 --> 00:20:28.625
About what you want from life?

380
00:20:29.750 --> 00:20:31.792
No. They don't.

381
00:20:31.875 --> 00:20:34.542
[chuckles]
Well. you must be the funny one.

382
00:20:34.625 --> 00:20:37.333
It's... just you two. right?

383
00:20:37.417 --> 00:20:39.833
Only you know about this mission failure.

384
00:20:40.417 --> 00:20:42.042
It's not something you brag about.

385
00:20:46.792 --> 00:20:47.917
[grunts]

386
00:20:48.000 --> 00:20:49.667
[screams]

387
00:20:53.375 --> 00:20:54.625
Hm.

388
00:20:54.708 --> 00:20:56.250
I think I murdered that guy.

389
00:20:56.917 --> 00:20:59.167
-I'm sorry.
-He was not a nice man.

390
00:21:00.958 --> 00:21:05.417
He's right. though.
About the Red Room. Dreykov...

391
00:21:05.500 --> 00:21:07.542
Dreykov's a pig. All of them are.

392
00:21:08.083 --> 00:21:10.750
But not you. You are a good man.

393
00:21:11.667 --> 00:21:13.667
-[sighs]
-[sirens approaching]

394
00:21:17.958 --> 00:21:19.208
Come on. We need to go.

395
00:21:19.292 --> 00:21:20.292
[thuds. grunts]

396
00:21:21.042 --> 00:21:23.542
Red Room Task Force. [grunts]

397
00:21:25.458 --> 00:21:26.583
You animals.

398
00:21:29.583 --> 00:21:30.625
Should we take the stairs?

399
00:21:31.333 --> 00:21:32.375
Window will be faster.

400
00:21:32.458 --> 00:21:33.875
-Let's go.
-Scum!

401
00:21:33.958 --> 00:21:36.208
Ah-ha. adventure!

402
00:21:36.792 --> 00:21:40.000
The intrepids are calling!

403
00:21:40.083 --> 00:21:41.083
Ya!

404
00:21:41.167 --> 00:21:44.500
Opa! Opa! Ya! Ya!

405
00:21:44.583 --> 00:21:48.125
So. our Russians spare the Starks.
but not baldy?

406
00:21:48.208 --> 00:21:50.625
Something about this math isn't adding up.

407
00:21:50.708 --> 00:21:52.708
[distant screaming]

408
00:21:54.708 --> 00:21:57.458
-[people scream]
-[Red Guardian grunts]

409
00:21:57.542 --> 00:21:59.375
A-ha-ha!

410
00:22:00.375 --> 00:22:01.375
[sighs]

411
00:22:01.458 --> 00:22:03.042
Nice moves. Okay.

412
00:22:05.167 --> 00:22:06.958
[both panting]

413
00:22:07.042 --> 00:22:08.667
-[indistinct chatter]
-Whoa!

414
00:22:09.625 --> 00:22:13.333
Again with the murdering.
You were doing so well.

415
00:22:14.417 --> 00:22:15.583
[slot machines pinging]

416
00:22:15.667 --> 00:22:17.500
-Jackpot.
-[all exclaiming]

417
00:22:17.583 --> 00:22:18.833
Mine. that's mine.

418
00:22:18.917 --> 00:22:20.500
Oh. brilliant.

419
00:22:22.167 --> 00:22:25.625
-Uh?
-What? I'm not getting overtime for this.

420
00:22:25.708 --> 00:22:28.042
I have one last chip of my own.

421
00:22:28.125 --> 00:22:29.792
-[man] Hey!
-[woman] What are they doing?

422
00:22:30.792 --> 00:22:32.042
Hut. hut. hut.

423
00:22:32.125 --> 00:22:33.125
[pants]

424
00:22:34.375 --> 00:22:36.542
-[horns honking]
-[Red Guardian] Whoa!

425
00:22:36.625 --> 00:22:37.708
[Goliath] Where are you goin'?

426
00:22:37.792 --> 00:22:39.833
Oh! This guy again?

427
00:22:39.917 --> 00:22:41.417
[Goliath] You can't outrun me.

428
00:22:41.500 --> 00:22:43.625
-I thought we were done with the big guy.
-[siren wails]

429
00:22:45.208 --> 00:22:46.208
Hey!

430
00:22:46.792 --> 00:22:48.917
-[grunting]
-[tires screeching]

431
00:22:50.667 --> 00:22:51.667
[grunts]

432
00:22:53.667 --> 00:22:54.833
-Hey!
-[Goliath] Up you go.

433
00:22:54.917 --> 00:22:56.583
[groaning]

434
00:22:57.167 --> 00:22:58.250
[Goliath] Hey. little man.

435
00:22:59.833 --> 00:23:00.917
[screams]

436
00:23:03.292 --> 00:23:04.292
[sighs in exhaustion]

437
00:23:05.000 --> 00:23:07.167
[both groaning]

438
00:23:07.792 --> 00:23:09.917
Defeat the capitalist giant.

439
00:23:11.833 --> 00:23:13.417
Uh-oh!

440
00:23:19.958 --> 00:23:21.500
[car alarms blaring]

441
00:23:21.583 --> 00:23:22.750
-Technique!
-Technique!

442
00:23:22.833 --> 00:23:24.167
[Red Guardian laughs]

443
00:23:24.250 --> 00:23:26.417
That's how we do it in Moscow.

444
00:23:27.042 --> 00:23:28.042
Thank you.

445
00:23:30.042 --> 00:23:32.708
Ah. Not bad. Pretty smooth.

446
00:23:34.208 --> 00:23:36.417
Is that it? Are they gone?

447
00:23:36.500 --> 00:23:38.250
Not gone. Cornered.

448
00:23:38.333 --> 00:23:39.625
Get the choppers over here.

449
00:23:39.708 --> 00:23:42.208
and call Las Vegas SWAT
to secure the exits on that building.

450
00:23:42.292 --> 00:23:43.750
I don't want a rat to get in or out.

451
00:23:43.833 --> 00:23:44.875
Get the choppers over here.

452
00:23:44.958 --> 00:23:47.208
Call Las Vegas SWAT
to secure the exits on the building.

453
00:23:47.292 --> 00:23:48.292
I don't want a...

454
00:23:50.000 --> 00:23:51.292
[panting]

455
00:23:52.125 --> 00:23:54.333
We did it. I think we lost them...

456
00:23:54.417 --> 00:23:55.542
[gunfire]

457
00:24:01.292 --> 00:24:02.792
The Red Room just arrived.

458
00:24:02.875 --> 00:24:05.083
Karpov can flip my switch. I'll be gone.

459
00:24:05.167 --> 00:24:06.292
I won't remember this.

460
00:24:07.708 --> 00:24:08.708
[sighs]

461
00:24:08.792 --> 00:24:09.917
[phone ringing]

462
00:24:11.833 --> 00:24:12.917
Ready to comply?

463
00:24:13.000 --> 00:24:16.667
[Karpov] <i>You failed your mission. soldier.
Dreykov warned you what would happen.</i>

464
00:24:19.125 --> 00:24:20.292
Dreykov?

465
00:24:20.375 --> 00:24:22.167
Dreykov put out a kill order on you.

466
00:24:22.250 --> 00:24:23.833
Uh. Oh?

467
00:24:23.917 --> 00:24:26.042
You mean he told you to...

468
00:24:26.125 --> 00:24:28.042
Take this and run.
I'll buy you time to escape.

469
00:24:28.125 --> 00:24:29.167
No. No.

470
00:24:29.250 --> 00:24:32.500
They betray me. I betray them!

471
00:24:32.583 --> 00:24:36.667
The Red Room has enough soldiers.
We'll fight together.

472
00:24:46.500 --> 00:24:47.500
[speaking Russian]

473
00:24:48.125 --> 00:24:49.417
What is happening?

474
00:24:49.500 --> 00:24:52.292
He's gonna make me kill you. Alexei.
He can force me.

475
00:24:52.750 --> 00:24:54.583
-[continues in Russian]
-[groans in pain]

476
00:24:56.417 --> 00:24:58.250
[whirring]

477
00:25:00.875 --> 00:25:01.875
[in Russian]

478
00:25:02.708 --> 00:25:06.958
Save yourself. This is America.
Anybody can be somebody in America.

479
00:25:07.042 --> 00:25:08.042
[in Russian]

480
00:25:08.917 --> 00:25:11.208
I remember that. thanks to you.

481
00:25:11.292 --> 00:25:13.250
But I know who I am.

482
00:25:13.333 --> 00:25:17.292
I am the friend
to the great Coney Island hero.

483
00:25:17.375 --> 00:25:19.583
-[in Russian]
-[groaning]

484
00:25:21.125 --> 00:25:22.125
[in Russian]

485
00:25:25.083 --> 00:25:26.792
On my count. gentlemen.

486
00:25:26.875 --> 00:25:28.000
[in Russian]

487
00:25:29.875 --> 00:25:30.958
Three.

488
00:25:31.042 --> 00:25:32.042
[in Russian]

489
00:25:34.167 --> 00:25:35.167
Two.

490
00:25:35.250 --> 00:25:36.250
[in Russian]

491
00:25:39.167 --> 00:25:40.208
One.

492
00:25:41.375 --> 00:25:43.000
[in Russian]

493
00:25:43.083 --> 00:25:44.500
[echoing]

494
00:25:58.292 --> 00:25:59.292
[gasps]

495
00:26:02.125 --> 00:26:04.125
[indistinct screaming. gunfire]

496
00:26:07.083 --> 00:26:09.292
[The Watcher]
<i>Fighting for survival. For acceptance.</i>

497
00:26:09.375 --> 00:26:10.917
<i>Fighting to be somebody.</i>

498
00:26:11.708 --> 00:26:14.375
<i>But in the end.
the fight is never the point.</i>

499
00:26:15.125 --> 00:26:18.250
<i>It's your friendships
that change the course of history.</i>

500
00:26:19.833 --> 00:26:21.917
<i>Even when they end.</i>

501
00:26:28.083 --> 00:26:29.333
[Dreykov] Where's Shostakov?

502
00:26:30.625 --> 00:26:32.542
Where is he?

503
00:26:32.625 --> 00:26:35.208
I told ya. He's dead.

504
00:26:36.042 --> 00:26:39.000
I want details. I want to see his body.

505
00:26:40.042 --> 00:26:41.875
He died a Russian hero.

506
00:26:45.625 --> 00:26:46.875
[speaking Russian]

507
00:26:48.875 --> 00:26:51.667
[groaning. screaming]

508
00:26:55.917 --> 00:27:00.917
[Bob] You're weak. children.
Blinded by American excess.

509
00:27:01.000 --> 00:27:03.833
Luckily. Coach Bob Toledo is here

510
00:27:03.917 --> 00:27:06.458
to make you fighters!

511
00:27:06.542 --> 00:27:07.542
[door opens]

512
00:27:14.875 --> 00:27:16.917
[Foster] An agent
recovered it at the scene.

513
00:27:18.083 --> 00:27:19.167
Thank you.

514
00:27:19.250 --> 00:27:21.833
But are you here to arrest me?

515
00:27:21.917 --> 00:27:23.000
No.

516
00:27:23.083 --> 00:27:25.500
S.H.I.E.L.D. was formed
after World War II.

517
00:27:25.583 --> 00:27:27.542
A war that Russia helped us win.

518
00:27:27.625 --> 00:27:29.917
We won. You helped.

519
00:27:30.583 --> 00:27:33.542
Well. I wanted to see if you'd help again.

520
00:27:34.125 --> 00:27:35.125
Seriously?

521
00:27:35.208 --> 00:27:36.375
[chuckles]

522
00:27:36.458 --> 00:27:37.500
Man...

523
00:27:38.208 --> 00:27:41.625
I could be persuaded
to fill out an application.

524
00:27:43.792 --> 00:27:46.792
[♪ "Avengers Theme" playing]

525
00:27:57.875 --> 00:28:00.750
[Red Guardian laughs] Whoa!

526
00:28:05.917 --> 00:28:06.917
[music stops]

527
00:28:07.792 --> 00:28:10.792
[♪ orchestral music playing]
